Vice President Kamala Harris addressed the importance of high-speed internet access in a teleconference. She highlighted the need for affordable and accessible internet for all Americans, including those living in rural areas and on Tribal lands. Harris announced $500 million in grants that will be awarded to Tribal applicants, including Tribal governments, Tribal schools, and utility companies in several states. She also mentioned the Affordable Connectivity Program, which offers a $75 monthly discount on internet bills for those living on Tribal lands. The Vice President emphasized the administration's commitment to connecting all Native communities with the internet to provide opportunities for healthier, happier, and more prosperous lives.